ented out, and source it after I've sourced my overlay's setup.bash. ", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>The title isn't great, but basically I would like the setup.sh broken into different files. </p>\n<p>Right now I am running a ROS Overlay, and if I source either the setup.sh in my overlay or the setup.sh from drcsim, they will clobber each others set ROS_PACKAGE_PATH. </p>\n<p>I was able to get it working fine if I created my own drcsim setup.sh file that just had \"step 1\" commented out, and source it after I've sourced my overlay's setup.bash. </p>", "type": "rendered"}, "assignee": {"display_name": "Brian Gerkey", "uuid": "{3d8b5763-9dad-4be7-85c2-a7ab6cd49173}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B3d8b5763-9dad-4be7-85c2-a7ab6cd49173%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B3d8b5763-9dad-4be7-85c2-a7ab6cd49173%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "https://avatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.net/557058:2e35028e-9ad8-4d6a-a3a5-275159a304a9/5fa9ec73-0fec-4860-a202-e34ae23b6a12/128"}}, "nickname": "Brian Gerkey", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:2e35028e-9ad8-4d6a-a3a5-275159a304a9"}, "state": "resolved", "version": null, "edited_on": null, "created_on": "2012-11-21T16:34:10.369418+00:00", "milestone": null, "updated_on": "2013-04-15T19:48:36.554666+00:00", "type": "issue", "id": 43}